explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the opening brackets. It iterates through the string, pushing the corresponding closing bracket onto the stack for each opening bracket. If it encounters a closing bracket that doesn't match the top of the stack, it returns false. Finally, it checks if the stack is empty, returning false if it's not (i.e., there are unmatched opening brackets).

